        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1036590753" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1985757212743934244">Dreamer by Patrick O&apos;Scheen is in a class by itself. This book is not at all what I expected, having only read the blurb. Instead, it was so much more. The characters are strong and easy to love. Magic, although ill, is the strongest of all. In this book, O&apos;Shceen takes us from the difficulties of Magic&apos;s illness and brings us happily into the gaming world of Dragons, Queens, Kings and numerous fantasy creatures. It was terrifically written, with mystery, suspense, battles, and of course, love. </span>
  <span id="freeText1985757212743934244" style="display:none">Dreamer by Patrick O'Scheen is in a class by itself. This book is not at all what I expected, having only read the blurb. Instead, it was so much more. The characters are strong and easy to love. Magic, although ill, is the strongest of all. In this book, O'Shceen takes us from the difficulties of Magic's illness and brings us happily into the gaming world of Dragons, Queens, Kings and numerous fantasy creatures. It was terrifically written, with mystery, suspense, battles, and of course, love. I thoroughly enjoyed it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1985757212743934244" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
